## Components

### The Shadcn/Radix Rule
Before building any interactive component, check if shadcn/ui already has it. If it does, use and customize it. Never build from scratch what already exists.

### Buttons
- ONE primary button per screen section
- Primary: solid fill, high contrast — the main action
- Secondary: outline or subtle fill — supporting actions
- Ghost/tertiary: text only — low priority
- Destructive: red variant — delete, remove, cancel
- Buttons and inputs MUST share the same height scale (32, 36, 40, 48px)
- Horizontal padding on buttons = 2× vertical padding
- Icon-only buttons MUST have `aria-label` and tooltip

### Every Component Needs Every State
Think through all states before considering a component done:
- **Default** — base appearance
- **Hover** — min 150ms transition, never instant
- **Focus** — visible focus ring, never `outline-none` without a replacement
- **Active/Pressed** — `active:scale-95` or equivalent tactile feedback
- **Disabled** — `opacity-40 cursor-not-allowed`, not interactive
- **Loading** — skeleton for content with known shape, spinner for actions
- **Empty** — see UX rules, always needs a CTA
- **Error** — clear, non-alarming, with recovery path

### Loading States
- Use skeletons (not spinners) for content that has a known shape
- Use spinners only for actions (form submit, file upload, processing)
- Never show a blank space while loading

### Tables and Data Display
- Left-align text columns, right-align number columns
- `tabular-nums` on every numeric column without exception
- Monospace font for IDs, codes, references, and technical values
- Consistent column widths — avoid columns that jump when data changes
- Sticky headers for scrollable tables
- Row hover state for scannability (`hover:bg-zinc-50`)
- Zebra striping OR subtle borders, never both
- Sortable headers with clear directional indicators

