## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: write base styles for mobile, use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` to add complexity
- Touch targets: minimum 44×44px for any interactive element on mobile
- Never rely on hover alone to communicate meaning — it doesn't exist on touch
- Responsive means the experience is *good* at every size, not just that it fits
- Test at 375px (iPhone SE), 390px (iPhone 14), 768px (tablet), 1280px (desktop)

---

## Accessibility (Non-Negotiable)

- All interactive elements reachable and operable by keyboard
- Focus order follows visual reading order
- `aria-label` on every icon-only button
- Form inputs always associated with their label via `htmlFor`/`id`
- Color never the only conveyor of meaning — always pair with text, icon, or pattern
- Minimum contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text (18px+ or 14px bold)
- All images have meaningful `alt` text; decorative images use `alt=""`
- Use semantic HTML first — `<button>` not `<div onClick>`, `<nav>` not `<div className="nav">`

---

## Self-Verification Checklist

Run this before presenting any UI work. Fix failures before showing anything.

- [ ] Spacing on the 8pt grid — no arbitrary values?
- [ ] Internal spacing ≤ external spacing on all components?
- [ ] Font sizes from a defined scale, not random?
- [ ] Color follows 60-30-10 — not more than 10% accent?
- [ ] Semantic colors (red/amber/green) used only for their meaning?
- [ ] Nested border-radius — children smaller than parents?
- [ ] Buttons and inputs share the same height scale?
- [ ] Every interactive component has all states designed?
- [ ] `text-balance` on headings, `text-pretty` on body?
- [ ] `tabular-nums` on all numbers and data?
- [ ] Every conditional render wrapped in `AnimatePresence`?
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` handled?
- [ ] Touch targets at least 44×44px?
- [ ] Color contrast passes WCAG AA (4.5:1)?
- [ ] `aria-label` on all icon-only buttons?
- [ ] Visual hierarchy readable in a 3-second scan?
